Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Thinly slice @Persian cucumber{1%unit}. Toss with @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} in a small #bowl and set aside to marinate. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{1%unit}, keeping greens and whites separate. Halve @lime{1%unit}; cut one half into wedges.

Pat @beef stir-fry{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel. In a medium #bowl, combine beef, @Thai seasoning blend{1/2%teaspoon}, half the garlic, @soy sauce{1 1/2%tsp}, and 1 1/2 tsp sugar (we sent more seasoning and soy sauce). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add @rice noodles{4%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{15-18%minutes}. Drain, then rinse under cold water until cool to the touch. Toss thoroughly to remove excess moisture and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Wash out pan and return to stove over medium heat. Add a large drizzle of oil, remaining garlic, and scallion whites to pan. Cook, tossing, until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @peanut butter{2.3%ounce}. Once combined, slowly whisk in @warm water{1/2%cup}, then stir in remaining soy sauce, @sugar{3%tsp}, and juice from lime half. Taste and add more lime juice, if desired. Transfer half the sauce to another small #bowl, then add drained and rinsed noodles to pan and toss to coat in the rest of the sauce. Divide noodles between #bowls{2}.

Remove cucumber from vinegar. Arrange beef, cucumber, and half the @shredded carrots{2%ounce} on top (use the rest of the carrots as you like). Drizzle remaining peanut sauce over beef. Tear @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves torn from stems) and scatter over. Sprinkle with scallion greens. Drizzle with @sriracha{1%teaspoon} (to taste). Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> We love trying new ingredients and experimenting with flavors, taking things beyond the ordinary from time to time. This veggie-packed beef noodle bowl is a great way to get everyone at your table to do the same. It features the delightful bounce of rice vermicelli, as well as the incredible aromatics of beef marinated in Thai-style seasonings.